parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently and without warning
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck
the vehicle does not respond to braking
and the speedometer needle may become difficult to read in bright daylight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control does not control the maximum speed
especially when going down hills
and the vehicle may accelerate beyond the set speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Difficulty reading the speedometer can cause accidents, especially during bright daylight hours.
symptoms: The speedometer needle is difficult to read due to the color of the needle and the dial's background
making it hard to determine the vehicle's speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring can cause loss of control, punctured tires, and accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Loud noise when starting the vehicle
broken or fractured coil spring
punctured tire
loss of control
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering/control arm can cause loss of control, accidents, and uneven tire wear.
symptoms: Broken or damaged steering/control arm
uneven tire wear
tilting wheels
loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when going down a hill with the cruise control on
the vehicle fails to maintain a set speed
the vehicle speeds up without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Paint Quality and Repair Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor paint quality and inadequate repair services can lead to a decrease in the vehicle's value, causing financial losses to the owner.
symptoms: The paint job looks awful
the vehicle requires multiple repaints
the repair process takes an extended period
the owner is not provided with a replacement vehicle during the repair process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brittle plastic material used in the front air dam can cause it to break easily, leading to potential damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: The front air dam breaks easily
the air dam is prone to damage from minor impacts
the dealer refuses to replace the damaged air dam
the customer is blamed for the damage.
